### Delete a Rose suite
Use `rosie delete`, e.g.
```bash
rosie delete u-bh???
```
See the [documentation](https://metomi.github.io/rose/doc/html/api/command-reference.html#rosie-delete).

This will delete a Rose suite if there are no uncommitted changes, or if the `--force` option is activated.

## Running a Rose suite

Navigate to the root directory of the Rose suite:
```bash
cd $HOME/roses/u-bhXXX
rose suite-run
```

Check progress with
```bash
cylc scan -c
```

Kill a running process
```bash
cylc stop --kill u-bh???
```
